 extent cosmic rays can be a\ndriving force behind winds is still an open issue and we discuss only in\npassing how a simple iso-thermal wind model could fit our data. Nevertheless,\nthe comparison with inferences from observations and theory looks promising\nwith radio continuum offering a complementary view on galactic winds. We finish\nwith a perspective on future observations and challenges lying ahead.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Nov 2021 14:31:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 18:07:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-16"}
